diminished {{c1::lingual::lingual/facial}} cusp.

Abscence of {{c2::ML}} groove
Lingual cusp size {{c3::variable}}

Mandibular First Premolar
Occlusal View
•Outline is {{c1::diamond-shaped::shape}}
•F-L {{c2::>::,>,<}} M-D dimension
•{{c4::Buccal}} cusp occupies {{c3::2/3::size}} of  occlusal surface*
•B and L cusp tips offset {{c4::mesially}}
•Occlusal table is {{c5::triangular::shape}}*

Mandibular First Premolar
Occlusal View
•Mesial outline indented by {{c5::ML groove}} - looks like “closed fist”
•Pronounced {{c4::transverse}} ridge*
•M and D pits may be connected by a {{c3::shallow central groove}}
•Distal fossa {{c2::larger, circular}}
•Mesial fossa more {{c1::linear}}

Mandibular First Premolar
Root form
•Usually {{c4::single::single/double}} rooted, bifurcation possible (but not common)
•Wider {{c2::F-L::F-L/M-D}} than {{c3::M-D::F-L/M-D}}
•Cross-section is {{c1::ovoid}}, wider buccally than lingually

Mandibular first premolar 
Lingual View
Presence of {{c1::ML}} groove.

Mandibular first premolar 
How to tell Right from Left
•Presence of {{c1::ML}} groove
•Mesial marginal ridge slopes {{c3::more than::less than/more than}} distal marginal ridge
•MB cusp ridge {{c2::shorter::shorter/longer}} than DB cusp ridge

Mandibular first premolar 
How to tell Right from Left
•Distal fossa {{c1::circular::circular/ovoid/linear}}, mesial is {{c2::linear::circular/ovoid/linear}}
•Lingual cusp offset towards {{c3::mesial::distal/mesial}}

Mandibular second premolar 
•Arch position: 5th from midline
•Universal {{c1::#20 and #29}}
•Proximal geometric form:  {{c2::rhomboidal}}
•Generally larger crown, {{c3::larger and longer root}}

Mandibular second premolar 
•May have two or three {{c1::cusps}}
•One {{c2::facial}}
•One or two {{c2::lingual}}
•Occlusal table resembles small {{c3::molar}}

Mandibular second premolar 
Development Timeline
•Initial calcification: {{c1::2¼ - 2½}} years
•Enamel completed: {{c2::6 - 7}} years
•Eruption: {{c3::11 - 12}} years
•Root completed: {{c4::13 - 14}} years

Mandibular second premolar 
Facial
•Resembles 1st from this view except:
•Cusp tip {{c1::not as sharp::sharp/not as sharp}}
•MB and DB cusp ridges {{c2::not as steeply inclined::steeply inclined/not as steeply inclined}}
•Cusp tip centered {{c3::mesiodistally::location}}*
•Mesial HOC near junction of {{c4::occlusal-middle third}}
•Distal HOC at junction of {{c4::occlusal-middle third }}

Mandibular second premolar 
Facial
•Lingual cusps generally {{c1::better::less/better}} developed than 1st
•Lingual HOC at {{c2::middle third to occlusal third::}}* (unique)
•Three cusp variety:
•ML cusp {{c3::larger::smaller/larger}} than DL
•Lingual groove {{c4::present::absent/absent}}

Mandibular Second Premolar
Mesial View
•Lingual inclination {{c1::less::more/less}} than 1st
•Buccal cusp tip is {{c2::facial::facial/lingual}} to tooth midline*
•Mesial marginal ridge nearly {{c1::horizontal::vertical/horizontal}}
•Mesial marginal groove present, {{c2::no::with/with no}} ML developmental groove
•Only {{c1::two::number}} cusps visible from this view

Mandibular Second Premolar
Distal View
•Distal marginal ridge more {{c1::cervical::occlusal/cervical}} than mesial
•{{c2::More::less/more}} of occlusal surface visible from this view
•All 3 cusp tips visible from this view (3-cusp variety)

Mandibular 2nd Premolar
Occlusal View
•General outline more {{c1::square}}
•{{c2::F-L::M-D/F-L}} > {{c2::M-D::M-D/F-L}} dimension
•{{c1::Less::more/less}} taper lingually than 1st*  (3-cusp variety possible slight divergence)
•Three occlusal groove patterns:
•Y-type (3 cusp variety)
•{{c3::U}}-type (2 cusp)
•{{c3::H}}-type (2 cusp)

Mandibular 2nd Premolar
Occlusal View
Three Cusp Variety
•Y shape groove pattern
•Formed by {{c1::lingual}} groove {{c1::joining::joining/separating}} central groove
•Only premolar with {{c1::lingual}} groove*
•Largest to smallest cusps: •{{c1::B, ML, DL}}

Mandibular 2nd Premolar
Occlusal View
Three Cusp Variety
•No typical {{c1::transverse}} ridge 
•3 pits: {{c1::mesial, central, distal}}*
•3 fossae:
•2 {{c2::triangular::shape}} fossae: {{c1::mesial and distal::location}}
•1 central fossa

Mandibular 2nd Premolar
Occlusal View
Two Cusp Variety
•U or H shape groove patterns
•More {{c1::rounded:sharp/rounded}} than 3-cusp variety
•Transverse ridge {{c2::present::absent}}
•No {{c1::lingual}} groove or central pit

Mandibular 2nd Premolar
Occlusal View
Two Cusp Variety
•Lingual cusp offset to {{c1::mesial::mesial/distal}}
•2 pits: {{c1::mesial and distal}}
•2 triangular fossae: {{c2::mesial and distal}}

Mandibular 2nd Premolar
Root form
•Normally {{c2::single}}, {{c1::bifurcation}} possible
•Root cross-section is {{c2::ovoid}}

Mandibular 2nd Premolar
Anomalies
{{c1::May be missing congenitally::major anomalie in this tooth}}

Mandibular 2nd Premolar
How to tell Right from Left
•ML cusp {{c1::larger::smaller/larger}} than DL (3-cusp)
•Lingual cusp offset {{c2::mesially::distally/mesially}} (2-cusp variety)
•Distal marginal ridge more {{c1::cervical::occlusal/cervical}} than mesial marginal ridge
•Root may have {{c2::distal::mesial/distal}} deflection

Mandibular 2nd Premolar
How to tell Right from Left
•ML cusp {{c1::larger::smaller/larger}} than DL (3-cusp)
•Lingual cusp offset {{c2::mesially::distally/mesially}} (2-cusp variety)
•Distal marginal ridge more {{c1::cervical::occlusal/cervical}} than mesial marginal ridge
•Root may have {{c2::distal::mesial/distal}} deflection

Mandibular molars
How to tell 1st from 2nd
•Greater disparity between {{c2::F and L::M and D}} cusp heights with 1st
•2nd typically {{c1::3-cusp::how many cusps}} variety
•{{c2::ML}} groove present in 1st
•Mesial marginal ridge slopes {{c1::more::less/more}} in 1st (45o)

Mandibular molars
How to tell 1st from 2nd
•Occlusal outline {{c1::more::more/less}} rounded in 1st, more {{c1::square::oval/square}} in 2nd
•Buccal cusp tip {{c2::centered::centered/ centered mesiodistally}} over root apex in 1st, facial of center in 2nd*
